text.paragraph:
Advise patients that they may develop fever and confusion as part of a syndrome resembling NMS and possibly with other clinical features (e.g., muscle rigidity, autonomic dysfunction, hyper- or hypotension, etc.). This fever and confusion syndrome may particularly occur with dose reductions or withdrawal of carbidopa, levodopa and entacapone tablets but may also develop after initiation of treatment. Advise patients to contact their healthcare provider if they wish to discontinue or decrease the dose of carbidopa, levodopa and entacapone tablets and to contact a health care provider if they develop fever and confusion [see Warnings and Precautions (
                     5.7
                     )].
